reviews.review: Really enjoyable ending to the saga! Plenty of fan service and homage to those who came before. Really fun movie!

So not near as bad as some critics are saying (no worse that marvels endgame, another movie that tried to dot all the I’s and cross all the t’s). I actually enjoyed the movie despite recognizing that it was also trying to cover all the bases. I heard someone review it as if it was on “prequel” level. No way, the prequels dragged, had horrible character development and used effects instead of plot. This movie still had you routing for its hero’s and even finding surprises as it unfolded. I would see it again.
Ehhh it wasn’t all that. It was okay.

Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker. No spoilers here. DO NOT listen to the critics. They know nothing. 

Simply amazing.  This movie blew me away. It was everything I hoped it would be, and even what I didn't know I wanted. This movie came the closest to capturing the magic of the original trilogy for me. More than either of the other sequel trilogy movies, and more than the prequels. This one FEELS like Star Wars. I laughed. I cried. I felt like the little kid I remember, crying while leaving the theater in 1980 because Han Solo was frozen in carbonite. 

I'm sad it's over...but I'm so happy it ended like this. It was amazing. I can't wait to go see it again.
plenty of action, and great closure to the story

No spoilers, I thought Episode 9 was an excellent movie. I genuinely enjoyed every minute of it. I cannot understand all the negative reviews and people trashing Rise of Skywalker. To each their own but I thought it was the best in the trilogy and that it concluded the story as best it could be finished. Maybe one or two nitpick things about the ending I could complain about but it doesn’t detract from how enjoyable this film was. I loved it.
IMO a great job was done in tying things together and wrapping loose ends.  Was very enjoyable.  At times a bit predictable and yet had some big surprises.

If you're a fan of campy, Star Wars "the force will be with you always" nostalgia then you'll love this. Not a stone was left unturned and it wraps up all nine movies nicely. There are twists and turns that keep you engaged the whole way. JJ Adams nailed it. The force is strong with this picture.
Fast paced (at times a bit too fast). Satisfying. Happy.

As a lifelong fan I have been with Star Wars through the ups and downs. The cinematography in this film is incredible as well as the essence that is captured. The emotion of the history of Star Wars displayed through all the characters and their arcs all concluded very nicely to finally close off this saga.
